The paper proposes index-based solutions for Density Peaks Clustering (DPC), which is a clustering approach used in data mining and machine learning. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely category as it deals with efficient storage and retrieval of large datasets. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories as DPC is a machine learning algorithm. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper proposes index-based solutions to improve the efficiency of DPC. Finally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely category as the paper deals with clustering rather than retrieval, but it is still relevant as clustering is often used as a pre-processing step in information retrieval.
